mAip6_TvtdY.title: 3 Arm Workouts
mAip6_TvtdY.description:
#1: How to Lose Arm Fat
On today's episode of XHIT, fitness trainer Rebecca-Louise shows you how to get toned arms in one workout. It's a quick but intense workout that hits your shoulders, biceps and triceps. Follow along to learn how to build muscle and shed fat in your arms. Leave us a comment and let us know what you thought!

#2: Toned Arms Workout
When you feel that burn in your arms you know you are getting a good workout. Today on XHIT, fitness trainer Rebecca-Louise shows you that you don't need to "do over a thousand" reps like Ron Burgundy to get a "deep burn." Grab your dumbbells and get ready to get an upper body pump! You stay classy, YouTubers!

#3: Total Arm Workout
On today's episode of XHIT, fitness trainer Rebecca-Louise shows you how to get toned arms in one workout. It's a quick but intense workout that hits your shoulders, biceps and triceps. Follow along to learn how to build muscle and shed fat in your arms. Leave us a comment and let us know what you thought!

gQ3EM0BXEoE.title: 3 Full Body Workouts: Easy, Intense, and Boot Camp
gQ3EM0BXEoE.description:
#1: Easy Full Body Workout
Today on XHIT we have a workout that pits you against yourself. How intense this workout will be is entirely dependent upon how much you put into it. Follow along as fitness trainer Rebecca-Louise takes you through a full body workout using resistance provided by your own body. 

#2: Intense Full Body Workout
On today's episode of XHIT, fitness trainer Cynthia Dallas shows you how burn a ton of calories in just a few minutes! Learn how to do a full body cardio workout that will slim your waist and tone your legs! Follow along and let us know what you thought!

#3: Full Body Boot Camp Workout
On today's episode of XHIT, fitness trainer Rebecca-Louise has a boot camp workout that is guaranteed to get you sweating and have your heart rate up! This full body workout will help tone your arms, legs, butt and abs! Please leave a comment and let us know what you thought!

lS6cdPVFTAI.title: Healthy Quinoa Recipe
lS6cdPVFTAI.description:
Sign up for our newsletter: http://goo.gl/UwnMd 

Subscribe: http://goo.gl/qR0gi  

On today's episode of XHIT, fitness trainer Kelsey Lee shows you how to make a healthy quinoa dish with carrots, spiced apples and red onions! Learn how to make a healthy, post workout snack that goes perfectly with today's full body workout! Follow along and let us know what you thought!

The Recipe:

1.Preheat the oven to 425°. In a small bowl, stir together coriander, pepper and ¾ teaspoon salt. In a 9--by-13-inch baking dish, add the carrots, apple, red onion and olive oil. Add the spice mixture and stir to combine.

2.In an 8- or 9-inch baking dish, add the rinsed quinoa and spread into an even layer. Place the quinoa and vegetables in the oven. Toast the quinoa until fragrant and golden, about 8 minutes, then pour 2 cups water over the quinoa and loosely cover the pan with a sheet of aluminum foil. Cook the quinoa until it uncoils and looks fluffy, 15 to 20 minutes. Remove the quinoa from the oven, fluff with a fork, re-cover with foil and set aside.

3.Meanwhile, continue to roast the vegetables, stirring occasionally, until the onions start to blacken around the edges and the carrots are tender, about 30 minutes total.

4.Transfer the quinoa to a serving dish. Stir in the remaining ¼ teaspoon salt, the lemon zest and lemon juice, then the parsley. Serve alongside the roasted vegetables.

Calories Per Serving: 250

Cook the quinoa until it uncoils and looks fluffy, 15 to 20 minutes. Remove the quinoa from the oven, fluff with a fork, re-cover with foil and set aside.

4.Transfer the quinoa to a serving dish. Stir in the remaining ¼ teaspoon salt, the lemon zest and lemon juice, then the parsley. Serve alongside the roasted vegetables.

b4esFx8-jeY.title: Squat to Chair - XFit Daily
b4esFx8-jeY.description:
How To Do The Move

1. Stand about a foot in front of a chair.  

2. Your feet should slightly wider than shoulder width apart. 

3. Cross your arms in front of you so that your hands are resting on your shoulders. 

4. Bend your knees and drop down to the chair. Keep your gaze straight ahead. 

5. Push back up to starting position and repeat the exercise.

aajhW7DD1EA.title: Exercise Tutorial - Step Up to Chair
aajhW7DD1EA.description:
How To Do The Move 

1. Get a chair and position it so its seat is facing you. 

2. Raise your right leg and step onto the seat with your right foot. 

3. Bring your left leg up so you're standing on the chair. 

4. Keeping your gaze straight ahead, step down with your right leg and then your left. 

5. Repeat on the other side.

iP2fjvG0g3w.title: Exercise Tutorial - V-Up
iP2fjvG0g3w.description:
How To Do The Move

1. Lie flat on your back with your arms to your sides. 

2. Lift your arms off the floor and position them behind your head. Your arms should remain straight. 

3. Slightly bend your knees and lift your legs off the floor, crunch forward and try to touch your toes. 

4. Lower your legs and bring your arms back behind you.

oWK_4kM-M9M.title: Exercise Tutorial - Staggered Arm Push-Up
oWK_4kM-M9M.description:
How To Do The Move

1. Get on your hands and knees in modified push-up position. Your hands should be about shoulder width apart. 

2. With your hands flat on the ground, bring your right arm forward just beyond your head and move your left arm slightly lower than shoulder height. 

3. Bend at the elbows and then raise yourself up. 

4. After a few repetitions, switch sides so that your left arm is ahead of you and your hand arm stays back.

zoeyTz5FKnw.title: Ski Jump - XFit Daily
zoeyTz5FKnw.description:
How To Do The Move 

1. Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart. 

2. Jump to the right and balance yourself on your right foot. Keep your left leg raised behind your right leg. 

3. Extend your right arm to the side. Your left arm, bent at the elbow, should be raised at chest level. 

4. Jump to your left, balancing yourself on your left foot. Keep your right leg raised behind your left leg. 

5. Extend your left arm to the side. Your right arm, bent at the elbow, should be raised at chest level.

p-bs9_urQJI.title: Exercise Tutorial - Starfish Plank
p-bs9_urQJI.description:
How To Do The Move

1. Lie on your right side. 

2. Push the ground away from you using your right forearm so you're in side plank position. 

3. Make sure your shoulder, hip and ankles are in a straight line. 

3. Raise your left arm so that your hand is directly above your head. At the same time, raise your left leg so it's about 2 feet above your right foot. 

4. Hold plank for 15 seconds and then switch sides.

a91XfAEhNIM.description:
Glad to see you again. You're in the right place to get your XFIT fix. We have three rounds of burpees, bird dogs, dive-bomber push-ups, lunges and floor bridges. 

XFIT Daily hits you with intense, full-body workouts five days a week. Trainers Jason Charchan and Michael Patarino lead you through a grueling series of fat-burning cardio movements and exercises that build strength and stability. XFIT: Get addicted.

About Our Trainers:
Jason Alexander Charchan, certified with the American Council on Exercise, has trained world-famous athletes, actors, models and more. He has appeared in Muscle & Fitness Magazine, competed in FAME and Musclemania, and appeared in fitness product commercials. Follow him on Twitter at https://twitter.com/jasonacharchan.

Michael Patarino is a experienced trainer and model in Los Angeles, CA. Follow him on Twitter at https://twitter.com/michaelpatarino.
